Well, the US, Brazil and Australia don't even acknowledge such a thing as manmade climate change exists! The US and Australia, in particular, are two of the countries with the highest cumulative CO2 emitted per person throughout history. Meanwhile, they won't even do anything until poorer countries and much more recently developed (or still developing) countries like India and China - with a tiny fraction of historic CO2 emitted per person (and much of that went to producing things consumed in rich countries) - cut their CO2. At least karma might be coming for Australia. It is already hot enough as it is, and they had devastating wild fires last year, and those fires are returning this year. If Australia becomes 100% desert, don't mourn it - they made their own bed. At least Europe is being progressive and countries like Germany should be praised.
